1
00:00:01,877 --> 00:00:05,797
NEWSREADER: Solar flare
activity has increased across space lanes 556

2
00:00:05,881 --> 00:00:08,133
and all commercial flights
are advised...

3
00:00:08,300 --> 00:00:11,428
(THROBBING HUM)

4
00:00:16,266 --> 00:00:18,268
(WHOOSHING)

5
00:00:27,236 --> 00:00:30,906
So, it's 200,000, it's a spaceship...
No, wait a minute, space station.

6
00:00:30,989 --> 00:00:32,032
And, er...

7
00:00:32,115 --> 00:00:33,700
Go try that gate over there!
Off you go.

8
00:00:34,284 --> 00:00:36,161
-200,0007 Right.
-200,000.

9
00:00:37,120 --> 00:00:38,956
Adam! Out you come.

10
00:00:40,290 --> 00:00:43,126
-Oh, my God.
-ROSE: Don't worry, you'll get used to it.

11
00:00:43,919 --> 00:00:45,754
-Where are we?
-ROSE: Good question.

12
00:00:45,837 --> 00:00:48,382
Let's see. So, um...

13
00:00:48,465 --> 00:00:51,885
Judging by the architecture,
I'd say we're around the year 200,000.

14
00:00:51,969 --> 00:00:54,054
-Uh-huh, yeah.
-ROSE: And if you listen...

15
00:00:54,137 --> 00:00:55,597
Engines.

16
00:00:55,681 --> 00:00:57,724
We're on some sort
of space station.

17
00:00:58,225 --> 00:01:00,060
Yeah, definitely
a space station.

18
00:01:00,644 --> 00:01:02,729
It's a bit warm in here,
they could turn the heating down.

19
00:01:03,689 --> 00:01:05,816
Tell you what,
let's try that gate. Come on.

20
00:01:14,241 --> 00:01:15,534
Here we go.

21
00:01:17,160 --> 00:01:18,328
And this is...

22
00:01:21,832 --> 00:01:23,584
ROSE: I'll let the Doctor
describe it.

23
00:01:25,168 --> 00:01:28,463
The Fourth Great and Bountiful
Human Empire. And there it is.

24
00:01:28,547 --> 00:01:30,382
Planet Earth, at its height.

25
00:01:31,466 --> 00:01:36,138
Covered with mega-cities, five
moons, population 96 billion,

26
00:01:36,388 --> 00:01:40,434
the hub of a galactic domain
stretching across a million planets,

27
00:01:40,601 --> 00:01:44,396
a million species,
with mankind right in the middle.

28
00:01:47,774 --> 00:01:49,067
He's your boyfriend.

29
00:01:49,610 --> 00:01:50,861
Not anymore.

30
00:01:54,197 --> 00:01:56,533
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

31
00:02:34,029 --> 00:02:36,698
DOCTOR: Come on, Adam,
open your mind. You're gonna like this

32
00:02:36,782 --> 00:02:40,118
fantastic period of history,
the human race at its most intelligent.

33
00:02:40,243 --> 00:02:41,745
Culture! Art! Politics!

34
00:02:41,828 --> 00:02:43,747
This era has got fine food,
good manners, the works...

35
00:02:43,830 --> 00:02:44,831
Out the way!

36
00:02:44,915 --> 00:02:48,210
MAN 1: Let's get to it.
Thank you very much, indeed.

37
00:02:48,293 --> 00:02:51,672
Somebody there? That's right. What do
you want, love? Keep it moving.

38
00:02:51,755 --> 00:02:54,549
-I'll be with you lot in a minute. Here you are.
-MAN 2: One at a time!

39
00:02:56,885 --> 00:03:00,847
Now what was it? Kronkburger with
cheese, kronkburger with pa jatos.

40
00:03:02,724 --> 00:03:04,935
Oi! You, mate! Stop pushing.

41
00:03:05,060 --> 00:03:07,938
Get back! I said back!

42
00:03:08,063 --> 00:03:11,274
-Fine cuisine?
-My watch must be wrong.

43
00:03:11,733 --> 00:03:13,360
No, it's fine. That's weird.

44
00:03:13,443 --> 00:03:16,655
That's what comes of showing off. Your
history's not as good as you thought it was.

45
00:03:16,738 --> 00:03:18,699
-My history is perfect.
-Well, obviously not.

46
00:03:18,782 --> 00:03:20,992
They're all human. What
about the millions of planets,

47
00:03:21,118 --> 00:03:22,703
millions of species,
where are they?

48
00:03:22,786 --> 00:03:25,288
Good question.
Actually, that is a good question.

49
00:03:25,747 --> 00:03:27,999
Adam, me old mate,
you must be starving!

50
00:03:28,125 --> 00:03:29,418
No, I'm just a bit time sick.

51
00:03:29,501 --> 00:03:32,129
You just need grub.
Oi, mate! How much is a kronkburger?

52
00:03:32,212 --> 00:03:35,298
Two credits twenty,
sweetheart. Now, join the queue!

53
00:03:35,757 --> 00:03:37,175
Money! We need money.

54
00:03:37,300 --> 00:03:38,802
Let's use a cash point.

55
00:03:42,723 --> 00:03:44,766
(WHIRRING)

56
00:03:48,979 --> 00:03:51,189
There you go, pocket money.
Don't spend it all on sweets.

57
00:03:51,648 --> 00:03:52,941
Well, how does it work?

58
00:03:53,024 --> 00:03:55,152
Go and find out,
stop nagging me!

59
00:03:55,444 --> 00:03:58,071
The thing is, Adam,
time travel's like visiting Paris.

60
00:03:58,155 --> 00:04:00,157
You can't just read
the guidebook, you gotta throw yourself in.

61
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:01,533
Eat the food,
use the wrong verbs,

62
00:04:01,616 --> 00:04:03,869
get charged double
and end up kissing complete strangers.

63
00:04:03,994 --> 00:04:05,162
Or is that just me?

64
00:04:05,746 --> 00:04:07,664
Stop asking questions,
go and do it!

65
00:04:08,832 --> 00:04:11,001
Off you go, then.
Your first date.

66
00:04:11,334 --> 00:04:13,253
You're gonna get a smack,
you are!

67
00:04:18,717 --> 00:04:21,511
Um, this is gonna sound daft,
but can you tell me where I am?

68
00:04:21,887 --> 00:04:23,346
Floor 139.

69
00:04:23,847 --> 00:04:26,516
-Could they write it any bigger?
-Floor 139 of what?

70
00:04:26,892 --> 00:04:28,351
Must have been a hell
of a party.

71
00:04:28,435 --> 00:04:31,104
-Are you on Satellite Five?
-What's Satellite Five?

72
00:04:32,022 --> 00:04:34,274
Come on, how could you
get on board without knowing where you are?

73
00:04:34,357 --> 00:04:35,484
Look at me, I'm stupid.

74
00:04:35,901 --> 00:04:37,486
Hold on, wait a minute.
Are you a test?

75
00:04:38,111 --> 00:04:41,031
-Some sort of management test kind of thing?
-You've got me.

76
00:04:41,114 --> 00:04:43,450
Well done.
You're too clever for me.

77
00:04:44,201 --> 00:04:45,994
We were warned about this
in basic training.

78
00:04:47,037 --> 00:04:49,873
All workers have to be versed
in company promotion.

79
00:04:51,041 --> 00:04:53,210
Right, fire away,
ask your questions.

80
00:04:53,502 --> 00:04:55,420
If it gets me to Floor
500, I'll do anything.

81
00:04:55,504 --> 00:04:57,047
Why? What happens
on Floor 5007

82
00:04:57,839 --> 00:04:59,549
The walls are made of gold.

83
00:05:00,342 --> 00:05:03,345
And you should know,
Mr Management.

84
00:05:03,428 --> 00:05:06,556
So, this is what we do.

85
00:05:09,726 --> 00:05:13,063
Latest news.
Sandstorms on the New Venus Archipelago,

86
00:05:13,146 --> 00:05:14,481
200 dead.

87
00:05:14,898 --> 00:05:17,484
Glasgow water riots
into their third day.

88
00:05:17,651 --> 00:05:20,320
Space lane 77 closed
by sunspot activity.

89
00:05:20,821 --> 00:05:24,825
And over on the Bad Wolf channel, the Face of
Boe has just announced he's pregnant.

90
00:05:24,908 --> 00:05:26,618
I get it.
You broadcast the news.

91
00:05:27,828 --> 00:05:29,079
We are the news.

92
00:05:29,454 --> 00:05:30,747
We're the journalists.

93
00:05:31,498 --> 00:05:33,375
We write it, package
it and sell it.

94
00:05:33,917 --> 00:05:37,921
600 channels, all coming out
of Satellite Five, broadcasting everywhere.

95
00:05:40,131 --> 00:05:41,466
Something

96
00:05:42,592 --> 00:05:43,718
is wrong.

97
00:05:46,638 --> 00:05:48,348
Something fictional.

98
00:05:53,144 --> 00:05:54,354
Those people.

99
00:05:54,437 --> 00:05:57,399
Nothing happens in the whole Human
Empire without it going through us.

100
00:05:58,024 --> 00:05:59,442
Security check.

101
00:06:00,443 --> 00:06:01,611
Go deep.

102
00:06:02,445 --> 00:06:05,282
VOICE OVER INTERCOM:
All staff are reminded that the canteen area

103
00:06:05,365 --> 00:06:08,702
now operates a
self-cleaning table system. Thank you.

104
00:06:08,785 --> 00:06:10,120
Try this, it's called Zaffic.

105
00:06:10,203 --> 00:06:13,456
It's nice, like, um,
a Slush Puppy.

106
00:06:13,915 --> 00:06:15,125
What flavour?

107
00:06:18,503 --> 00:06:19,671
It's sort of beef.

108
00:06:19,796 --> 00:06:21,089
Oh, my God!

109
00:06:21,172 --> 00:06:22,799
(LAUGHING)

110
00:06:24,426 --> 00:06:26,052
It's like everything's gone.

111
00:06:26,136 --> 00:06:27,846
Home, family...

112
00:06:27,929 --> 00:06:29,431
Everything.

113
00:06:30,974 --> 00:06:34,603
This helps.
The Doctor gave it a bit of a top-up.

114
00:06:34,686 --> 00:06:36,062
Who's back home,
your mum and dad?

115
00:06:36,479 --> 00:06:37,647
Yeah.

116
00:06:37,939 --> 00:06:38,940
Phone them up.

117
00:06:39,816 --> 00:06:42,193
But that's 198,000 years ago.

118
00:06:42,319 --> 00:06:44,404
Honestly, try it.
Go on.

119
00:06:45,530 --> 00:06:47,490
-Is there a code for planet Earth?
-Just dial!

120
00:06:48,283 --> 00:06:49,743
(BEEPING)

121
00:06:50,327 --> 00:06:51,912
(TELEPHONE RINGS)

122
00:06:56,249 --> 00:06:57,417
WOMAN: I'm sorry we're not in.

123
00:06:57,500 --> 00:06:59,628
-It's her.
-Please leave a message. Thanks, bye!

124
00:07:00,003 --> 00:07:01,004
(BEEPS)

125
00:07:01,212 --> 00:07:02,505
Hi!

126
00:07:02,631 --> 00:07:03,840
It... It's me.

127
00:07:05,508 --> 00:07:08,929
I've sort of gone traveling.

128
00:07:09,512 --> 00:07:13,808
I met these people,
and we're traveling together.

129
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:17,437
But, um, I'm fine.
And I'll call you later.

130
00:07:17,854 --> 00:07:19,356
Love you. Bye.

131
00:07:19,522 --> 00:07:20,523
(LAUGHS)

132
00:07:20,649 --> 00:07:23,193
(KLAXON SOUNDS)

133
00:07:25,445 --> 00:07:27,697
Oi, Mutt and Jeff! Over here!

134
00:07:38,875 --> 00:07:40,210
COMPUTER:
Security check cleared.

135
00:07:40,293 --> 00:07:42,087
No, something's wrong.

136
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:45,131
I can taste it.

137
00:07:46,883 --> 00:07:49,427
A tiny little shift
in the information.

138
00:07:50,261 --> 00:07:52,430
Someone down there
shouldn't be here.

139
00:07:54,224 --> 00:07:56,434
Double check. Triple check.

140
00:07:57,394 --> 00:07:58,687
Follow them.

141
00:08:01,064 --> 00:08:02,857
Now, everybody behave.

142
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:05,110
We have a management
inspection.

143
00:08:05,235 --> 00:08:06,569
How do want it? By the book?

144
00:08:06,861 --> 00:08:08,071
Right from scratch, thanks.

145
00:08:08,405 --> 00:08:10,740
Okay. So, ladies, gentlemen,

146
00:08:11,032 --> 00:08:13,243
multisex, undecided or robot,

147
00:08:13,410 --> 00:08:16,204
my name
is Cathica Santini Khadeni.

148
00:08:16,955 --> 00:08:18,081
That's Cathica with a C,

149
00:08:18,164 --> 00:08:21,960
in case you wanna write
to Floor 500, praising me, and please do.

150
00:08:22,919 --> 00:08:24,671
Now, please feel free
to ask any questions.

151
00:08:24,754 --> 00:08:26,965
The process of news gathering
must be open,

152
00:08:27,048 --> 00:08:29,092
honest and beyond bias.

153
00:08:29,175 --> 00:08:30,552
That's company policy.

154
00:08:31,761 --> 00:08:33,930
Actually, um, it's the law.

155
00:08:35,348 --> 00:08:37,434
Yes, thank you, Suki.

156
00:08:38,101 --> 00:08:39,436
Okay, keep it calm.

157
00:08:39,561 --> 00:08:41,229
Don't show off for the guests.

158
00:08:41,604 --> 00:08:43,064
Here we go.

159
00:08:44,399 --> 00:08:45,483
And...

160
00:08:47,068 --> 00:08:48,278
Engage safety.

161
00:08:48,737 --> 00:08:51,406
(HUMMING)

162
00:09:07,172 --> 00:09:08,173
And three...

163
00:09:08,673 --> 00:09:11,092
Two... And spike!

164
00:09:16,097 --> 00:09:17,348
Compressed information

165
00:09:17,474 --> 00:09:18,975
streaming into her.

166
00:09:19,434 --> 00:09:22,812
Reports from every city,
every country, every planet,

167
00:09:23,063 --> 00:09:25,023
and they all get packaged
inside her head.

168
00:09:25,690 --> 00:09:27,400
She becomes part
of the software.

169
00:09:27,484 --> 00:09:29,319
Her brain is the computer!

170
00:09:30,070 --> 00:09:32,238
If it all goes through her,
she must be a genius.

171
00:09:32,322 --> 00:09:34,657
Nah, she wouldn't remember
any of it.

172
00:09:35,575 --> 00:09:37,327
There's too much.
Her head would blow up.

173
00:09:38,036 --> 00:09:39,662
The brain's the processor.

174
00:09:40,246 --> 00:09:41,748
Soon as it closes,
she forgets.

175
00:09:42,040 --> 00:09:44,334
What about all these people
round the edge?

176
00:09:44,417 --> 00:09:46,336
They've all got tiny little
chips in their head

177
00:09:46,419 --> 00:09:50,507
connecting them to her,
and they transmit 600 channels.

178
00:09:51,091 --> 00:09:54,010
Every single fact
in the Empire beams out of this place.

179
00:09:56,471 --> 00:09:58,139
Now, that's what I call power.

180
00:09:59,432 --> 00:10:02,060
COMPUTER: Analysis confirmed.
Security breach.

181
00:10:02,811 --> 00:10:05,730
I knew it. Which one?

182
00:10:06,231 --> 00:10:08,691
It's someone inside
that room. Which one?

183
00:10:11,653 --> 00:10:13,154
Isolating breach.

184
00:10:15,198 --> 00:10:17,033
Come on. Show me. Who is it?

185
00:10:19,786 --> 00:10:22,580
ROSE: You all right?
ADAM: I can see her brain.

186
00:10:23,081 --> 00:10:25,333
-Do you wanna get out?
-No, but this...

187
00:10:26,084 --> 00:10:28,378
This technology, it's...
It's amazing.

188
00:10:29,003 --> 00:10:30,380
This technology's wrong.

189
00:10:32,966 --> 00:10:34,175
Trouble?

190
00:10:34,968 --> 00:10:36,219
Oh, yeah.

191
00:10:38,513 --> 00:10:39,514
(ZAPPING)

192
00:10:39,722 --> 00:10:42,433
That's it! Ho, ho, ho, yes!

193
00:10:42,517 --> 00:10:45,895
She's the liar.
Intercept and scan.

194
00:10:47,397 --> 00:10:48,606
Gotcha!

195
00:10:54,404 --> 00:10:55,405
(GASPS)

196
00:10:55,530 --> 00:10:58,366
Come off it, Suki,
I wasn't even halfway. What was that for?

197
00:10:58,449 --> 00:11:00,201
Sorry.
It must've been a glitch.

198
00:11:02,328 --> 00:11:04,122
Her information's
been tampered with.

199
00:11:05,456 --> 00:11:07,500
There's a second biography
hidden underneath.

200
00:11:07,584 --> 00:11:11,796
- (CREATURE GROWLING)
-Yes, sir. Absolutely, sir.

201
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:15,967
Yeah, her data was encrypted but there's no
way we could have found her sooner.

202
00:11:16,050 --> 00:11:18,636
-(GROWLING)
-Yeah, sorry, I... Yeah, sorry, sir.

203
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:20,930
-(GROWLING)
-Yeah, absolutely.

204
00:11:22,849 --> 00:11:24,767
Get her up here! Now!

205
00:11:26,227 --> 00:11:27,520
WOMAN: Promotion.

206
00:11:28,563 --> 00:11:30,815
CATHICA: Come on,
this is it, come on!

207
00:11:31,566 --> 00:11:33,109
Oh, my God, make it me!

208
00:11:33,193 --> 00:11:36,571
Come on, say my name,
say my name, say my name!

209
00:11:38,573 --> 00:11:39,616
Promotion for...

210
00:11:40,825 --> 00:11:44,913
Suki Macrae Cantrell.
Please proceed to Floor 500.

211
00:11:44,996 --> 00:11:48,082
I don't believe it! Floor 500!

212
00:11:49,459 --> 00:11:51,586
How the hell
did you manage that? I'm above you!

213
00:11:52,545 --> 00:11:54,631
I don't know,
I just applied on the off chance.

214
00:11:56,257 --> 00:11:57,800
And they've said yes!

215
00:11:58,009 --> 00:12:01,471
So not fair. I've been applying
to Floor 500 for three years.

216
00:12:01,971 --> 00:12:03,389
What's Floor 5007

217
00:12:04,307 --> 00:12:06,142
The walls are made of gold.

218
00:12:08,645 --> 00:12:10,730
SUKI: Cathica,
I'm gonna miss you.

219
00:12:11,147 --> 00:12:13,900
-Floor 500. Thank you.
-I didn't do anything.

220
00:12:13,983 --> 00:12:15,610
You're my lucky charm.

221
00:12:15,818 --> 00:12:17,111
All right, I'll hug anyone.

222
00:12:17,195 --> 00:12:18,738
(SUKI LAUGHING)

223
00:12:19,822 --> 00:12:21,282
Come on, it's not that bad.

224
00:12:21,366 --> 00:12:23,576
What, with the...
The head thing?

225
00:12:23,660 --> 00:12:25,245
Yeah, well,
she's closed it now.

226
00:12:25,328 --> 00:12:26,746
Yeah, but...

227
00:12:28,414 --> 00:12:30,833
It's everything.
It freaks me out.

228
00:12:32,585 --> 00:12:34,587
-And I just need to...
-(BEEPING)

229
00:12:34,671 --> 00:12:36,506
Ah, if I could just...
(SIGHS)

230
00:12:36,631 --> 00:12:39,092
Cool down,
sort of acclimatise.

231
00:12:39,509 --> 00:12:40,718
How do you mean?

232
00:12:42,178 --> 00:12:45,932
Maybe I could just
go and sit on the observation deck.

233
00:12:46,015 --> 00:12:47,016
Will that be all right?

234
00:12:47,850 --> 00:12:51,521
Soak it in, you know.
Pretend I'm a citizen of the year 200,000.

235
00:12:52,230 --> 00:12:53,606
Do you want me
to come with you?

236
00:12:54,482 --> 00:12:56,192
No, no, you stick
with the Doctor.

237
00:12:59,862 --> 00:13:01,447
You'd rather be with him.

238
00:13:04,367 --> 00:13:06,869
It's gonna take a better man
than me to get between you two.

239
00:13:08,746 --> 00:13:09,998
Anyway...

240
00:13:10,081 --> 00:13:11,874
I'LL be on the deck.

241
00:13:12,542 --> 00:13:14,711
Here you go,
take the Tardis key.

242
00:13:14,794 --> 00:13:16,921
You know, just in case
it gets a bit too much.

243
00:13:17,547 --> 00:13:19,549
Yeah, like it's not weird
in there.

244
00:13:25,221 --> 00:13:27,015
(BEEPING)

245
00:13:30,560 --> 00:13:32,478
Oh, my God.
I've got to go, I can't keep them waiting.

246
00:13:32,562 --> 00:13:33,563
I'm sorry.

247
00:13:36,733 --> 00:13:38,276
Say goodbye to Steve for me.

248
00:13:39,694 --> 00:13:40,903
Bye!

249
00:13:42,405 --> 00:13:43,948
Good riddance.

250
00:13:44,240 --> 00:13:46,909
You're talking like you'll never see her again.
She's only going upstairs.

251
00:13:47,076 --> 00:13:50,413
We won't. Once you go to Floor 500,
you never come back.

252
00:14:02,592 --> 00:14:04,594
-Have you ever been up there?
-Can't.

253
00:14:04,927 --> 00:14:07,555
You need a key for the lift
and you only get a key with promotion.

254
00:14:07,764 --> 00:14:10,391
No one gets to 500,
except for the chosen few.

255
00:14:22,111 --> 00:14:23,613
(PANTING)

256
00:14:44,717 --> 00:14:45,718
(BEEPING)

257
00:14:45,802 --> 00:14:47,136
(GASPS)

258
00:14:49,013 --> 00:14:50,264
(GRUNTING)

259
00:15:48,573 --> 00:15:49,615
(SUKI SCREAMS)

260
00:15:49,991 --> 00:15:50,992
(GASPS)

261
00:16:58,100 --> 00:16:59,227
Who are you?

262
00:16:59,852 --> 00:17:01,103
I'm the Editor.

263
00:17:03,064 --> 00:17:04,273
What's happening?

264
00:17:04,857 --> 00:17:08,194
There are bodies out there.
What's going on?

265
00:17:09,111 --> 00:17:12,073
While we're asking questions,
would you please confirm your name?

266
00:17:13,616 --> 00:17:15,868
My name is
Suki Macrae Cantrell.

267
00:17:16,536 --> 00:17:19,330
I was born 199°'89,

268
00:17:19,497 --> 00:17:21,457
in the Independent Republic
of Morocco.

269
00:17:21,541 --> 00:17:22,625
Liar!

270
00:17:22,917 --> 00:17:26,128
Hobbies include reading
and archaeology.

271
00:17:26,462 --> 00:17:28,589
I'm not an expert or anything,
I just like digging.

272
00:17:28,673 --> 00:17:29,674
Liar!

273
00:17:29,966 --> 00:17:32,510
I want to work for
Satellite Five because

274
00:17:32,635 --> 00:17:34,929
my sister can't
afford university.

275
00:17:35,638 --> 00:17:37,139
And the pay-scheme
Is really good...

276
00:17:37,306 --> 00:17:38,307
Liar!

277
00:17:41,018 --> 00:17:42,395
Let's look at the facts,
shall we?

278
00:17:43,104 --> 00:17:44,146
Ah.

279
00:17:44,230 --> 00:17:46,774
Hidden behind a genetic graft,
but that's still you.

280
00:17:47,358 --> 00:17:51,362
Eva Saint Julienne,
last surviving member of the Freedom Fifteen.

281
00:17:52,572 --> 00:17:55,241
Hmm, self-declared anarchist.
Is that right?

282
00:17:55,324 --> 00:17:57,326
Who controls Satellite Five?

283
00:18:02,957 --> 00:18:04,041
(LAUGHING)

284
00:18:05,418 --> 00:18:06,919
There's the truth.

285
00:18:08,796 --> 00:18:12,508
The Freedom Foundation has been
monitoring Satellite Five's transmissions.

286
00:18:13,676 --> 00:18:16,721
We have absolute proof
that the facts are being manipulated.

287
00:18:16,846 --> 00:18:19,015
You are lying to the people.

288
00:18:19,098 --> 00:18:20,683
Ooh, I love it.
Say it again.

289
00:18:21,183 --> 00:18:22,852
This whole system is corrupt.

290
00:18:24,729 --> 00:18:26,355
Who do you represent?

291
00:18:27,064 --> 00:18:29,025
I'm merely a humble slave.

292
00:18:29,191 --> 00:18:31,068
I answer
to the Editor In Chief.

293
00:18:32,528 --> 00:18:36,198
-Who is he, where is he?
-He's overseeing everything.

294
00:18:36,282 --> 00:18:38,117
Literally everything.

295
00:18:38,534 --> 00:18:41,871
If you don't mind, I'm gonna
have to refer this upwards.

296
00:18:43,456 --> 00:18:45,833
(CREATURE GROWLING)

297
00:18:48,085 --> 00:18:50,504
-What is that?
-Your boss.

298
00:18:50,880 --> 00:18:52,715
This has always
been your boss.

299
00:18:52,923 --> 00:18:55,092
Since the day you were born.

300
00:18:56,093 --> 00:18:57,553
(FIRING GUN)

301
00:18:58,554 --> 00:19:00,306
(SCREAMING)

302
00:19:16,572 --> 00:19:17,823
Give me access.

303
00:19:23,245 --> 00:19:24,664
Give me...

304
00:19:28,709 --> 00:19:29,960
I can learn anything.

305
00:19:35,841 --> 00:19:38,636
Let's try, uh, computers.

306
00:19:39,553 --> 00:19:41,722
From the 21st century
to the present day,

307
00:19:41,806 --> 00:19:44,809
give me the history
of the microprocessor.

308
00:19:49,772 --> 00:19:50,773
Oh, my God.

309
00:19:51,315 --> 00:19:54,235
Look, they only give us 20 minutes
maintenance. Can't you give it a rest?

310
00:19:54,402 --> 00:19:56,821
But you've never been to another
floor? Not even one floor down?

311
00:19:58,739 --> 00:20:00,408
I went to floor 16
when I first arrived.

312
00:20:00,491 --> 00:20:02,493
That's medical, that's when
I got my head done. And then I...

313
00:20:03,119 --> 00:20:04,245
I came straight here.

314
00:20:04,328 --> 00:20:07,832
Satellite Five, you work, eat, and sleep on
the same floor, and that's it, that's all.

315
00:20:09,834 --> 00:20:11,293
You're not management,
are you?

316
00:20:11,544 --> 00:20:12,795
At last! She's clever.

317
00:20:14,213 --> 00:20:16,966
Yeah, well, whatever it is,
don't involve me. I don't know anything.

318
00:20:17,216 --> 00:20:19,135
-Don't you even ask?
-Why would I?

319
00:20:19,218 --> 00:20:20,636
You're a journalist!

320
00:20:21,721 --> 00:20:23,013
Why's all the crew human?

321
00:20:24,140 --> 00:20:25,433
What's that got
to do with anything?

322
00:20:25,641 --> 00:20:27,143
There's no aliens on board.
Why?

323
00:20:27,893 --> 00:20:29,353
I don't know.
No real reason.

324
00:20:29,770 --> 00:20:32,148
-They're not banned or anything.
-Then where are they?

325
00:20:34,525 --> 00:20:37,278
I suppose Immigration's tightened up.
It's had to, what with all the threats.

326
00:20:37,361 --> 00:20:38,362
What threats?

327
00:20:39,613 --> 00:20:41,949
I don't know, all of them,
usual stuff.

328
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:46,287
And the price of space warp
doubled, so that kept the visitors away.

329
00:20:46,579 --> 00:20:48,581
Oh, and the government
on Chavic Five collapsed,

330
00:20:48,664 --> 00:20:50,166
so that lot stopped coming, you see?

331
00:20:51,292 --> 00:20:53,461
Just lots of little reasons,
that's all.

332
00:20:53,544 --> 00:20:56,338
Adding up to one, great big fact.
And you didn't even notice.

333
00:20:57,339 --> 00:20:59,633
Doctor, I think, if there
was any sort of conspiracy,

334
00:20:59,717 --> 00:21:01,510
Satellite Five
would have seen it.

335
00:21:01,761 --> 00:21:03,763
-We see everything.
-I can see better.

336
00:21:04,013 --> 00:21:06,682
This society's the wrong shape,
even the technology.

337
00:21:06,766 --> 00:21:08,267
-It's cutting edge!
-It's backwards.

338
00:21:08,350 --> 00:21:09,852
There's a great big door
in your head.

339
00:21:09,935 --> 00:21:12,563
-You should've chucked this out years ago!
-So what you think's going on?

340
00:21:12,688 --> 00:21:14,857
It's not just this space station,
it's the whole attitude.

341
00:21:14,940 --> 00:21:16,108
It's the way people think.

342
00:21:16,567 --> 00:21:19,862
The Great and Bountiful Human Empire is
stunted. Something's holding it back.

343
00:21:20,154 --> 00:21:21,614
And how would you know?

344
00:21:21,739 --> 00:21:22,740
Trust me.

345
00:21:23,157 --> 00:21:25,451
Humanity's been
set back about 90 years.

346
00:21:25,618 --> 00:21:27,620
When did Satellite Five
start broadcasting?

347
00:21:29,205 --> 00:21:30,706
91 years ago.

348
00:21:35,795 --> 00:21:38,547
Mum, Dad, keep this message,
okay?

349
00:21:38,714 --> 00:21:41,008
Whatever you do,
don't erase it.

350
00:21:41,509 --> 00:21:43,052
Save it, you got that?

351
00:21:49,183 --> 00:21:52,520
The microprocessor became
redundant in the year 2019,

352
00:21:52,603 --> 00:21:54,730
replaced by a system called,

353
00:21:54,814 --> 00:21:58,025
SMT, that's Single Molecule
Transcription.

354
00:21:58,943 --> 00:22:01,153
No, no, no, no, no!
What are you doing?

355
00:22:01,237 --> 00:22:04,907
Come back, come...
Why are you doing that?

356
00:22:07,284 --> 00:22:09,578
What's Floor 16?
What's down there?

357
00:22:36,856 --> 00:22:38,107
Sorry, um...

358
00:22:38,440 --> 00:22:41,569
Floor 16, that's, um...
What do you cover?

359
00:22:42,152 --> 00:22:43,612
Medical non-emergency.

360
00:22:44,321 --> 00:22:47,199
Right, yeah, wrong floor.
I'm having technical difficulties.

361
00:22:47,283 --> 00:22:49,285
My screen keeps freezing,
locking me out.

362
00:22:49,952 --> 00:22:53,289
No, that's medical. There must be
something wrong with your chip.

363
00:22:55,082 --> 00:22:57,459
Yes!
Yeah, of course, yeah!

364
00:22:59,044 --> 00:23:00,170
I haven't got one.

365
00:23:00,921 --> 00:23:02,590
No wonder you can't
get a screen to work.

366
00:23:03,382 --> 00:23:04,800
What are you, a...

367
00:23:05,843 --> 00:23:06,844
Student?

368
00:23:08,220 --> 00:23:10,014
Yes. Yeah, I'm, um...

369
00:23:11,098 --> 00:23:13,309
I'm on a research project...

370
00:23:13,642 --> 00:23:15,811
From the University of Mars.

371
00:23:17,605 --> 00:23:19,315
The Martian boondocks,
typical.

372
00:23:19,481 --> 00:23:20,482
Yep!
(LAUGHS)

373
00:23:21,150 --> 00:23:22,568
Well, you still need chipping.

374
00:23:23,611 --> 00:23:25,821
So, does that mean, like...

375
00:23:26,780 --> 00:23:27,990
Brain surgery?

376
00:23:28,365 --> 00:23:30,117
That's an old-fashioned
phrase.

377
00:23:30,451 --> 00:23:31,702
But it's the same thing, yes.

378
00:23:31,827 --> 00:23:33,621
Oh!
Okay, never mind.

379
00:23:35,164 --> 00:23:36,665
But if I get a chip,

380
00:23:38,167 --> 00:23:40,419
that means I could use
any computer?

381
00:23:40,502 --> 00:23:41,962
Absolutely.

382
00:23:43,422 --> 00:23:45,382
You'll have to pay for it.

383
00:23:45,966 --> 00:23:47,301
They've stopped subsidising.

384
00:23:47,426 --> 00:23:50,512
Oh, right, sorry.
Wasting your time.

385
00:23:50,846 --> 00:23:51,972
Thanks.

386
00:23:54,975 --> 00:23:56,185
Hold on.

387
00:23:58,187 --> 00:23:59,355
Can I use this?

388
00:24:00,648 --> 00:24:01,982
That'll do nicely.

389
00:24:02,983 --> 00:24:05,402
It all comes down
to two basic types.

390
00:24:05,861 --> 00:24:08,614
Type one, the head chip,

391
00:24:08,739 --> 00:24:11,992
inserted into the back
of the skull, 100 credits.

392
00:24:12,868 --> 00:24:13,994
There's the chip.

393
00:24:14,954 --> 00:24:17,748
Tiny, invisible, no scarring.

394
00:24:18,499 --> 00:24:21,210
Type two is the full
info-spike.

395
00:24:21,335 --> 00:24:22,962
Oh, um, that's the...

396
00:24:25,172 --> 00:24:27,007
-Thing.
-That's the one.

397
00:24:27,716 --> 00:24:29,510
It does cost 10,000.

398
00:24:30,177 --> 00:24:32,554
Oh, well I, um,
I couldn't afford it then.

399
00:24:33,389 --> 00:24:37,768
Not at all.
Turns out you've got unlimited credit.

400
00:24:40,938 --> 00:24:43,148
No, but I...
Well, I couldn't have it done.

401
00:24:43,232 --> 00:24:46,568
I mean, that's gotta hurt,
hasn't it?

402
00:24:47,361 --> 00:24:49,738
Painless.
Contractual guarantee.

403
00:24:51,240 --> 00:24:53,117
No, my, my mate's
waiting upstairs,

404
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:54,952
I can't have major surgery.
(LAUGHS)

405
00:24:56,370 --> 00:24:57,746
It takes ten minutes.

406
00:24:58,205 --> 00:25:01,375
That sort of money buys
a very fast pico-surgeon.

407
00:25:02,459 --> 00:25:03,669
No, but I...

408
00:25:04,712 --> 00:25:06,171
I couldn't though, no.

409
00:25:10,092 --> 00:25:13,178
Type one, you can interface
with a simple computer.

410
00:25:13,637 --> 00:25:17,891
Type two,
you are the computer.

411
00:25:19,101 --> 00:25:21,061
You can transmit any
piece of information

412
00:25:21,145 --> 00:25:22,771
from the archive
of Satellite Five

413
00:25:22,896 --> 00:25:27,109
which is just about the entire
history of the human race.

414
00:25:29,153 --> 00:25:30,404
Now...

415
00:25:32,948 --> 00:25:34,408
Which one's it going to be?

416
00:25:37,911 --> 00:25:39,621
We're so gonna get in trouble.

417
00:25:42,833 --> 00:25:45,335
You're not allowed to touch
the mainframe, we'll get told off.

418
00:25:45,461 --> 00:25:46,754
Rose, tell her to button it.

419
00:25:47,129 --> 00:25:49,882
You'll just vandalise the place,
someone's gonna notice.

420
00:25:51,508 --> 00:25:52,885
EDITOR: I don't understand.

421
00:25:53,927 --> 00:25:55,804
We did a full security scan,

422
00:25:55,888 --> 00:25:59,141
that man was there when
we found Suki Macrae Cantrell.

423
00:26:00,267 --> 00:26:02,061
There were no
indications about him.

424
00:26:02,978 --> 00:26:04,480
And yet here he is.

425
00:26:05,856 --> 00:26:07,858
Clearly acting
outside the parameters.

426
00:26:10,694 --> 00:26:11,779
Fascinating.

427
00:26:12,654 --> 00:26:14,490
(CREATURE GROWLING)

428
00:26:14,948 --> 00:26:16,408
Yes, sir.

429
00:26:18,744 --> 00:26:19,953
Absolutely.

430
00:26:21,121 --> 00:26:22,164
At once.

431
00:26:23,040 --> 00:26:24,041
Check him.

432
00:26:24,124 --> 00:26:27,336
Double check him,
triple check him, quadruple!

433
00:26:31,006 --> 00:26:33,217
This is nothing to do with me,
I'm going back to work.

434
00:26:33,342 --> 00:26:36,220
Go on then, see ya!
I can't just leave you, can I?

435
00:26:36,345 --> 00:26:39,389
If you wanna be useful, get them to turn
the heating down, it's boiling.

436
00:26:40,432 --> 00:26:42,434
What's wrong with this place?
Can't they do something about it?

437
00:26:42,518 --> 00:26:44,686
I don't know, we keep asking.
Something to do with the turbines.

438
00:26:44,937 --> 00:26:46,355
Something to do
with the turbines.

439
00:26:46,730 --> 00:26:48,023
But I don't know.

440
00:26:48,357 --> 00:26:50,317
Exactly. I give up
on you, Cathica.

441
00:26:50,400 --> 00:26:53,028
Now, Rose, look at Rose,
Rose is asking the right kind of questions.

442
00:26:53,153 --> 00:26:55,197
-Ah, thank you.
-Why is it so hot?

443
00:26:55,656 --> 00:26:57,157
One moment you're worried
about the Empire,

444
00:26:57,241 --> 00:26:59,201
and the next minute,
it's the central heating.

445
00:26:59,326 --> 00:27:01,912
Oh, never underestimate plumbing.
Plumbing is very important.

446
00:27:01,995 --> 00:27:02,996
(CRACKLES)

447
00:27:05,707 --> 00:27:07,835
COMPUTER:
Security scan complete.

448
00:27:08,919 --> 00:27:11,088
-Well, who is he?
-He is no one.

449
00:27:11,880 --> 00:27:12,923
(LAUGHS)

450
00:27:13,048 --> 00:27:14,633
What does that mean?

451
00:27:15,634 --> 00:27:16,927
He is no one.

452
00:27:17,386 --> 00:27:18,804
What, you mean
he has a fake ID?

453
00:27:20,013 --> 00:27:21,807
He has no identification.

454
00:27:22,516 --> 00:27:25,727
But everyone's registered.
We have a census for the entire Empire!

455
00:27:26,854 --> 00:27:28,063
He is no one.

456
00:27:28,397 --> 00:27:29,898
What, he doesn't exist?

457
00:27:30,232 --> 00:27:32,276
-Not anywhere?
-He is no one.

458
00:27:32,359 --> 00:27:33,527
What about the blonde?

459
00:27:34,736 --> 00:27:36,864
-She is no one.
-Both of them?

460
00:27:37,072 --> 00:27:38,073
(CHUCKLES)

461
00:27:38,991 --> 00:27:42,202
Well, we all know what happens
to non-entities.

462
00:27:42,327 --> 00:27:43,579
They get promoted.

463
00:27:46,165 --> 00:27:47,166
Bring them up!

464
00:27:49,042 --> 00:27:52,588
Here we go, Satellite Five.
Pipes and plumbing. Look at the layout.

465
00:27:53,547 --> 00:27:54,923
CATHICA: This is ridiculous.

466
00:27:55,632 --> 00:27:57,426
You've got access to
the computer's core.

467
00:27:57,718 --> 00:28:00,220
You could look at the archive,
the news, the stock exchange...

468
00:28:01,346 --> 00:28:04,141
-And you're looking at pipes?
-But there's something wrong.

469
00:28:05,684 --> 00:28:07,227
-I suppose.
-Why, what is it?

470
00:28:08,604 --> 00:28:09,980
The ventilation system.

471
00:28:10,689 --> 00:28:13,108
Cooling ducts, ice filters.
All working flat out.

472
00:28:14,026 --> 00:28:16,111
Channelling massive
amounts of heat down.

473
00:28:16,320 --> 00:28:18,488
-All the way from the top.
-Floor 500.

474
00:28:18,614 --> 00:28:21,241
Something up there
is generating tons and tons of heat.

475
00:28:21,825 --> 00:28:24,953
Well, I don't know about you,
but I feel like I'm missing out on a party.

476
00:28:25,329 --> 00:28:26,955
It's all going on upstairs.

477
00:28:27,080 --> 00:28:29,208
-Fancy a trip?
-You can't, you need a key.

478
00:28:29,291 --> 00:28:32,920
Keys are just codes,
and I've got the codes right here. Here we go.

479
00:28:33,503 --> 00:28:37,049
Override 215.9.

480
00:28:39,092 --> 00:28:40,636
CATHICA: How come it's giving
you the code?

481
00:28:41,720 --> 00:28:43,138
Someone up there likes me.

482
00:28:43,931 --> 00:28:45,849
(LAUGHING)

483
00:28:51,188 --> 00:28:52,856
I told you it was painless.

484
00:28:54,274 --> 00:28:56,318
No scarring, you see?

485
00:28:57,527 --> 00:28:58,904
Perfect success.

486
00:29:00,697 --> 00:29:02,324
How do I activate it?

487
00:29:03,033 --> 00:29:04,576
It's a personal choice.

488
00:29:05,035 --> 00:29:06,495
Some people whistle.

489
00:29:06,787 --> 00:29:10,207
I know one man who triggers it
with Oh, Danny Boy.

490
00:29:12,501 --> 00:29:14,086
But you're set
on default for now.

491
00:29:14,920 --> 00:29:16,213
That's a click of the fingers.

492
00:29:17,214 --> 00:29:18,840
So, you mean I just...

493
00:29:21,093 --> 00:29:22,094
Click.

494
00:29:26,974 --> 00:29:28,809
-Come on, come with us.
-No way!

495
00:29:28,892 --> 00:29:31,520
-Bye!
-Well, don't mention my name.

496
00:29:32,187 --> 00:29:34,273
When you get in trouble,
just don't involve me.

497
00:29:35,941 --> 00:29:38,819
That's her gone, Adam's given up,
looks like it's just you and me.

498
00:29:38,902 --> 00:29:40,320
-Yeah.
-Good.

499
00:29:41,029 --> 00:29:42,030
Yep.

500
00:29:43,907 --> 00:29:44,908
(BEEPING)

501
00:29:57,587 --> 00:29:59,464
Oh, my God! I'm gonna be sick!

502
00:30:00,340 --> 00:30:02,384
(RETCHING)

503
00:30:09,266 --> 00:30:10,600
Special offer.

504
00:30:11,018 --> 00:30:13,687
We installed the vomit-o-matic
at the same time.

505
00:30:13,937 --> 00:30:16,398
Nano-termites have been placed
in the lining of your throat.

506
00:30:16,606 --> 00:30:18,150
In the event of sickness,

507
00:30:20,152 --> 00:30:21,903
they freeze the waste.

508
00:30:34,875 --> 00:30:36,376
The walls are not made
of gold.

509
00:30:37,878 --> 00:30:39,254
You should go back downstairs.

510
00:30:40,297 --> 00:30:41,465
Tough.

511
00:30:59,941 --> 00:31:02,069
I started without you.

512
00:31:02,444 --> 00:31:03,779
This is fascinating.
(LAUGHS)

513
00:31:04,404 --> 00:31:07,240
Satellite Five contains
every piece of information

514
00:31:07,324 --> 00:31:10,035
within the Fourth Great
and Bountiful Human Empire.

515
00:31:10,285 --> 00:31:14,915
Birth certificates, shopping habits,
bank statements, but you two...

516
00:31:15,874 --> 00:31:17,125
You don't exist.

517
00:31:17,209 --> 00:31:19,002
(CHUCKLES)
There's not a trace.

518
00:31:19,378 --> 00:31:22,714
No birth, no job,
not the slightest kiss.

519
00:31:23,006 --> 00:31:26,259
How can you walk through
the world and not leave a single footprint?

520
00:31:26,843 --> 00:31:28,470
Suki! Suki!

521
00:31:29,388 --> 00:31:30,389
Hello?

522
00:31:31,098 --> 00:31:32,682
Can you hear me? Suki?

523
00:31:33,183 --> 00:31:35,685
-What have you done to her?
-I think she's dead.

524
00:31:38,563 --> 00:31:39,940
But she's working.

525
00:31:40,357 --> 00:31:42,984
They've all got chips in their head,
and the chips keep going.

526
00:31:43,110 --> 00:31:45,153
-Like puppets.
-Oh!

527
00:31:46,029 --> 00:31:47,447
You are full of information.

528
00:31:47,531 --> 00:31:49,699
But it's only fair we get
some information back.

529
00:31:49,825 --> 00:31:52,744
Because, apparently
you're no one. (CHUCKLES)

530
00:31:52,828 --> 00:31:54,913
It's so rare
not to know something.

531
00:31:55,997 --> 00:31:57,082
Who are you?

532
00:31:57,499 --> 00:31:59,960
It doesn't matter,
'cause we're off. Nice to meet you.

533
00:32:00,043 --> 00:32:01,128
Come on!

534
00:32:03,797 --> 00:32:04,840
Tell me who you are.

535
00:32:05,173 --> 00:32:08,093
Since that information is keeping us alive,
I'm hardly gonna say, am I?

536
00:32:09,010 --> 00:32:11,847
Well, perhaps my
Editor-In-Chief can convince you otherwise.

537
00:32:12,013 --> 00:32:13,181
And who's that?

538
00:32:15,559 --> 00:32:16,977
It may interest you to know

539
00:32:17,060 --> 00:32:20,105
that this is not the Fourth Great
and Bountiful Human Empire.

540
00:32:20,188 --> 00:32:22,899
In fact, it's not actually
human at all.

541
00:32:23,650 --> 00:32:25,861
It's merely a place
where humans happen to live.

542
00:32:25,944 --> 00:32:26,945
(CREATURE GROWLING)

543
00:32:27,028 --> 00:32:29,698
Yep. Yep.

544
00:32:31,241 --> 00:32:32,325
Sorry!

545
00:32:33,702 --> 00:32:35,579
It's a place where humans
are allowed to live

546
00:32:36,037 --> 00:32:37,998
by kind permission
of my client.

547
00:32:38,081 --> 00:32:40,709
-(SNAPPING)
-(GROWLING)

548
00:32:49,968 --> 00:32:51,052
What is that?

549
00:32:51,470 --> 00:32:54,306
You mean that thing's in
charge of Satellite Five?

550
00:32:54,764 --> 00:32:58,977
"That thing"”, as you put it,
is in charge of the human race.

551
00:32:59,728 --> 00:33:03,106
For almost 100 years,
mankind has been shaped and guided.

552
00:33:03,190 --> 00:33:06,485
His knowledge and ambition,
strictly controlled by its broadcast news.

553
00:33:06,568 --> 00:33:09,404
Edited by my superior,
your master,

554
00:33:10,572 --> 00:33:12,365
and humanity's quiding light,

555
00:33:12,908 --> 00:33:16,286
the Mighty Jagrafess of the
Holy Hadrojassic Maxarodenfoe.

556
00:33:17,496 --> 00:33:19,080
I call him Max.

557
00:33:39,684 --> 00:33:40,685
(BEEPING)

558
00:33:56,952 --> 00:34:00,956
Create a climate of fear,
and it's easy to keep the borders closed.

559
00:34:01,456 --> 00:34:03,792
It's just a matter
of emphasis.

560
00:34:04,709 --> 00:34:06,545
The right word
in the right broadcast,

561
00:34:06,628 --> 00:34:09,214
repeated often enough,
can destabilize an economy.

562
00:34:09,297 --> 00:34:11,341
Invent an enemy.
Change a vote.

563
00:34:11,883 --> 00:34:14,678
So all the people on
Earth are like slaves?

564
00:34:15,303 --> 00:34:17,764
Well, now,
there's an interesting point.

565
00:34:17,973 --> 00:34:21,893
Is a slave a slave if
he doesn't know he's enslaved?

566
00:34:21,977 --> 00:34:22,978
Yes.

567
00:34:23,144 --> 00:34:25,772
Oh, I was hoping
for a philosophical debate.

568
00:34:25,855 --> 00:34:27,482
Is that all I'm gonna get?
llYeSll?

569
00:34:27,607 --> 00:34:28,984
-Yes.
-(EDITOR LAUGHS)

570
00:34:29,150 --> 00:34:30,318
You're no fun.

571
00:34:30,819 --> 00:34:33,238
Let me out of these manacles.
You'll find out how much fun I am.

572
00:34:33,488 --> 00:34:35,615
Oh, he's tough, isn't he?
(CHUCKLES)

573
00:34:35,991 --> 00:34:38,285
But come on!
Isn't it a great system?

574
00:34:38,368 --> 00:34:40,120
You've got to admire it,
just a little bit.

575
00:34:40,912 --> 00:34:43,623
You can't hide something on this scale,
somebody must've noticed.

576
00:34:44,499 --> 00:34:46,459
From time to time,
someone, yes.

577
00:34:46,543 --> 00:34:49,879
But the computer chip system
allows me to see inside their brains.

578
00:34:50,380 --> 00:34:53,174
I can see the smallest doubt
and crush it.

579
00:35:10,233 --> 00:35:12,068
And then they just carry on,

580
00:35:12,152 --> 00:35:15,155
living the life,
strutting about downstairs

581
00:35:15,238 --> 00:35:18,450
and all over the surface
of the Earth, like they're so individual.

582
00:35:18,533 --> 00:35:21,077
When, of course, they're not.
They're just cattle.

583
00:35:22,412 --> 00:35:24,706
In that respect, the Jagrafess
hasn't changed a thing.

584
00:35:25,498 --> 00:35:29,044
But what about you?
You're not a Jagra... Uh, belly...

585
00:35:29,210 --> 00:35:32,005
-Jagrafess.
-Jagrafess. You're not a Jagrafess.

586
00:35:32,088 --> 00:35:33,089
You're human.

587
00:35:33,214 --> 00:35:35,800
Yeah, well, simply being human
doesn't pay very well.

588
00:35:36,384 --> 00:35:38,178
But you couldn't have done this
all on your own.

589
00:35:38,261 --> 00:35:39,512
No! (CHUCKLES)

590
00:35:39,596 --> 00:35:42,057
I represent a consortium
of banks.

591
00:35:42,766 --> 00:35:44,976
Money prefers
a long-term investment.

592
00:35:45,393 --> 00:35:49,439
Also the Jagrafess
needed a little hand to, um, install himself.

593
00:35:50,023 --> 00:35:52,692
DOCTOR: No wonder,
creature that size. What's its lifespan?

594
00:35:52,817 --> 00:35:53,818
EDITOR: 3,000 years.

595
00:35:53,902 --> 00:35:56,613
DOCTOR: That's one hell
of a metabolism, generating all that heat.

596
00:35:57,447 --> 00:35:59,574
That's why
Satellite Five's so hot.

597
00:35:59,658 --> 00:36:01,701
You pump it out the creature,
channel it downstairs.

598
00:36:01,785 --> 00:36:04,329
Jagrafess stays cool,
stays alive.

599
00:36:05,330 --> 00:36:08,208
Satellite Five is one great
big life-support system.

600
00:36:11,419 --> 00:36:12,587
(DIALLING)

601
00:36:14,589 --> 00:36:17,175
Me again.
Don't wipe this message.

602
00:36:17,258 --> 00:36:19,010
It's just gonna sound like
white noise.

603
00:36:19,094 --> 00:36:21,596
But save it,
"cause I can translate it, okay?

604
00:36:26,142 --> 00:36:27,310
Three,

605
00:36:27,394 --> 00:36:28,728
two,

606
00:36:29,062 --> 00:36:31,189
one, and spike!

607
00:36:36,277 --> 00:36:38,446
But that's why
you're so dangerous.

608
00:36:38,947 --> 00:36:42,367
Knowledge is power,
but you remain unknown. (CHUCKLES)

609
00:36:42,951 --> 00:36:44,786
-(ELECTRICAL WHIRRING)
-Who are you?

610
00:36:48,540 --> 00:36:49,541
(DOG BARKING)

611
00:36:54,629 --> 00:36:56,423
Leave her alone!
I'm the Doctor.

612
00:36:56,506 --> 00:36:59,092
She's Rose Tyler,
we're nothing, we're just wandering.

613
00:36:59,175 --> 00:37:01,344
-Tell me who you are!
-I've just said!

614
00:37:01,428 --> 00:37:03,054
Yeah, but who do you work for?

615
00:37:03,138 --> 00:37:05,390
Who sent you?
Who knows about us?

616
00:37:05,473 --> 00:37:06,558
Who exactly...

617
00:37:12,981 --> 00:37:14,232
Time Lord.

618
00:37:14,691 --> 00:37:15,692
What?

619
00:37:15,775 --> 00:37:19,446
Oh, yes!
The last of the Time Lords.

620
00:37:19,529 --> 00:37:21,156
And his traveling machine.

621
00:37:22,157 --> 00:37:24,784
With his little human girl
from long ago.

622
00:37:24,868 --> 00:37:27,871
-Don't know what you're talking about.
-Time travel!

623
00:37:28,663 --> 00:37:30,707
(SCREAMS)

624
00:37:33,501 --> 00:37:35,336
Someone's been telling
you lies.

625
00:37:36,546 --> 00:37:38,506
Young master Adam Mitchell?

626
00:37:39,340 --> 00:37:41,718
(ADAM SCREAMING)

627
00:37:44,512 --> 00:37:46,139
Oh, my God, his head.

628
00:37:47,015 --> 00:37:48,141
What the hell's he done?

629
00:37:49,350 --> 00:37:51,019
What the hell's he gone
and done?

630
00:37:52,103 --> 00:37:54,355
They're reading his mind,
he's telling them everything.

631
00:37:54,689 --> 00:37:57,609
And through him,
I know everything about you.

632
00:37:57,692 --> 00:38:01,029
Every piece of information
in his head is now mine.

633
00:38:01,529 --> 00:38:04,032
And you have infinite
knowledge, Doctor.

634
00:38:04,699 --> 00:38:06,409
The Human Empire is tiny

635
00:38:06,493 --> 00:38:07,994
compared to what you've seen
in your

636
00:38:08,077 --> 00:38:10,497
T-A-R-D-I-S.

637
00:38:10,580 --> 00:38:11,581
Tardis!

638
00:38:11,706 --> 00:38:13,500
Well, you'll never get your hands on it,
I'll die first!

639
00:38:13,583 --> 00:38:16,878
Well, die all you like,
I don't need ya. I've got the key.

640
00:38:26,930 --> 00:38:28,556
You and your boyfriends!

641
00:38:28,640 --> 00:38:31,559
Today, we are the headlines.

642
00:38:31,726 --> 00:38:33,228
We can rewrite history.

643
00:38:33,686 --> 00:38:35,814
We could prevent mankind
from ever developing.

644
00:38:36,272 --> 00:38:38,233
And no one's gonna stop you.

645
00:38:38,399 --> 00:38:41,402
Because you bred a human race
which doesn't bother to ask questions.

646
00:38:41,736 --> 00:38:44,447
Stupid little slaves
believing every lie.

647
00:38:44,614 --> 00:38:48,868
They'll just trot right into the slaughter house
if they're told it's made of gold.

648
00:38:49,077 --> 00:38:50,995
(MAX GROWLING)

649
00:39:05,426 --> 00:39:06,761
Disengage safety.

650
00:39:09,514 --> 00:39:10,849
(ALARM BEEPING)

651
00:39:11,641 --> 00:39:12,892
What's happening?

652
00:39:14,269 --> 00:39:17,522
Maximum access,
override Floor 139.

653
00:39:21,609 --> 00:39:23,903
And... Spike!

654
00:39:26,406 --> 00:39:28,116
Someone's disengaged
the safety.

655
00:39:29,367 --> 00:39:30,952
Who's that?

656
00:39:35,582 --> 00:39:37,625
-It's Cathica.
-And she's thinking.

657
00:39:37,959 --> 00:39:39,627
She's using what she knows.

658
00:39:40,295 --> 00:39:41,796
Terminate her access.

659
00:39:42,130 --> 00:39:43,965
Everything I told her
about Satellite Five,

660
00:39:44,048 --> 00:39:46,175
the pipes, the filters,
she's reversing it.

661
00:39:46,968 --> 00:39:48,803
Look at that.
It's getting hot.

662
00:39:49,971 --> 00:39:51,514
I said, terminate.

663
00:39:54,934 --> 00:39:56,728
Burn out her mind.

664
00:39:57,896 --> 00:39:59,314
Oh, no, you don't!

665
00:40:00,189 --> 00:40:02,650
You should've
promoted me years back.

666
00:40:28,176 --> 00:40:29,552
She's venting the heat
up here.

667
00:40:30,178 --> 00:40:32,305
The Jagrafess needs
to stay cool,

668
00:40:32,388 --> 00:40:34,724
and now it's sitting
on top of a volcano! (LAUGHS)

669
00:40:37,644 --> 00:40:38,728
(GROWLING)

670
00:40:38,853 --> 00:40:40,730
Yes, I'm trying, sir.

671
00:40:40,855 --> 00:40:43,274
But I don't know how she did it,
it's impossible.

672
00:40:43,733 --> 00:40:45,526
A member of staff
with an idea!

673
00:40:49,280 --> 00:40:50,698
(SHRIEKING)

674
00:40:54,619 --> 00:40:56,454
-What do I do?
-Flick the switch!

675
00:40:57,372 --> 00:40:58,373
(WHIRRING)

676
00:41:00,249 --> 00:41:01,459
(SHRIEKING)

677
00:41:02,502 --> 00:41:04,170
(ALARM BLARING)

678
00:41:11,219 --> 00:41:12,428
(SHRIEKING)

679
00:41:14,013 --> 00:41:15,932
Oi, mate!
You want to bank on a certainty?

680
00:41:16,307 --> 00:41:17,976
Massive heat
in a massive body,

681
00:41:18,309 --> 00:41:19,560
massive bang!

682
00:41:20,311 --> 00:41:21,562
See you in the headlines!

683
00:41:21,980 --> 00:41:23,231
(WHOOSHING)

684
00:41:28,152 --> 00:41:30,738
Actually, sir,
if it's all the same to you, I think I'll resign.

685
00:41:30,822 --> 00:41:31,906
Bye, then.

686
00:41:34,867 --> 00:41:35,910
Let go of me!

687
00:41:36,536 --> 00:41:37,870
(RUMBLING)

688
00:41:38,663 --> 00:41:40,081
(CIRCUITS SCRAMBLING)

689
00:41:43,084 --> 00:41:44,502
(SHRIEKING)

690
00:41:45,795 --> 00:41:47,255
Let go of me!

691
00:41:47,672 --> 00:41:49,007
(GRUNTS) Let go of me!

692
00:41:52,301 --> 00:41:53,594
-(CREATURE GROWLING)
-(SCREAMING)

693
00:42:13,114 --> 00:42:14,699
We're just gonna go.
I hate tidying up.

694
00:42:14,782 --> 00:42:16,284
Too many questions.
You'll manage.

695
00:42:16,534 --> 00:42:18,453
You'll have to stay and explain it.
No one's gonna believe me.

696
00:42:18,619 --> 00:42:20,455
Well, they might start
believing a lot of things now.

697
00:42:20,538 --> 00:42:22,915
Human race should accelerate.
All back to normal.

698
00:42:23,082 --> 00:42:24,167
What about your friend?

699
00:42:24,709 --> 00:42:26,210
He's not my friend.

700
00:42:28,671 --> 00:42:29,922
Now, don't...

701
00:42:30,506 --> 00:42:32,467
I'm all right now.
Much better.

702
00:42:33,718 --> 00:42:35,136
And I've got the key.
Look, it's...

703
00:42:35,470 --> 00:42:36,804
And, well...

704
00:42:36,971 --> 00:42:39,223
It all worked out
for the best, didn't it?

705
00:42:41,225 --> 00:42:45,605
You know, it's not actually my fault,
because you were in charge.

706
00:42:48,357 --> 00:42:50,151
It's my house. I'm home.

707
00:42:50,276 --> 00:42:52,278
(CHUCKLES)
Oh, my God, I'm home!

708
00:42:53,154 --> 00:42:55,948
Blimey. I thought you
were gonna chuck me out of an airlock.

709
00:42:56,157 --> 00:42:58,326
Is there something else
you want to tell me?

710
00:42:58,451 --> 00:43:00,495
No. Erm, what do you mean?

711
00:43:02,997 --> 00:43:04,332
The archive of Satellite Five.

712
00:43:04,499 --> 00:43:06,501
One second of that message
could have changed the world.

713
00:43:11,255 --> 00:43:12,256
(WHIRRING)

714
00:43:15,510 --> 00:43:17,011
That's it, then. See ya.

715
00:43:17,887 --> 00:43:19,680
-How do you mean, "See ya"?
-As in, goodbye.

716
00:43:19,931 --> 00:43:21,015
What about me?

717
00:43:21,140 --> 00:43:22,642
You can't just go.
I've got my head.

718
00:43:22,725 --> 00:43:24,435
I've got a chip type two.
My head opens.

719
00:43:24,519 --> 00:43:25,728
-What, like this?
-(WHIRRS)

720
00:43:27,021 --> 00:43:28,064
Don't!

721
00:43:28,272 --> 00:43:29,732
Don't do what?

722
00:43:31,359 --> 00:43:32,527
Stop it!

723
00:43:33,694 --> 00:43:36,739
All right now, Doctor.
That's enough. Stop it.

724
00:43:38,825 --> 00:43:40,034
Thank you.

725
00:43:40,952 --> 00:43:43,079
-0
- (CHUCKLES) Sorry, I couldn't resist.

726
00:43:44,038 --> 00:43:45,998
The whole of history
could have changed because of you.

727
00:43:46,082 --> 00:43:47,208
I just wanted to help.

728
00:43:47,375 --> 00:43:48,459
You were helping yourself.

729
00:43:48,584 --> 00:43:51,879
And I'm sorry.
And I've said I'm sorry, and I am, I really am.

730
00:43:52,171 --> 00:43:53,464
But you can't just
leave me like this.

731
00:43:53,589 --> 00:43:56,801
Yes, I can. 'Cause if you show that head to
anyone, they'll dissect you in seconds.

732
00:43:57,051 --> 00:43:59,470
You'll have to lead a very quiet life.
Keep out of trouble.

733
00:43:59,554 --> 00:44:01,722
Be average. Unseen. Good luck.

734
00:44:02,056 --> 00:44:03,474
But I wanna come with you.

735
00:44:04,475 --> 00:44:05,893
I only take the best.

736
00:44:05,977 --> 00:44:07,311
I've got Rose.

737
00:44:08,729 --> 00:44:09,897
ADAM: Rose, Rose!

738
00:44:10,481 --> 00:44:12,400
-Oh, my God!
-ADAM'S MUM: Who's that?

739
00:44:12,900 --> 00:44:15,736
-Geoff, is that you?
-It's me, Mum.

740
00:44:15,820 --> 00:44:17,446
ADAM: Don't come in,
wait there a minute.

741
00:44:17,613 --> 00:44:21,033
Oh, my Lord! You never told me
you were coming home!

742
00:44:21,534 --> 00:44:23,494
ADAM'S MUM: Hold on,
I'll just take my coat off.

743
00:44:24,245 --> 00:44:25,705
I wish you'd told me
you were coming home.

744
00:44:25,788 --> 00:44:27,373
Rose, take me with you.

745
00:44:27,582 --> 00:44:29,375
ADAM'S MUM: I would've
got your favourite tea in.

746
00:44:29,542 --> 00:44:30,751
(THROBBING HUM)

747
00:44:32,003 --> 00:44:33,337
What's that noise?

748
00:44:33,462 --> 00:44:34,672
Have you left
the back door open?

749
00:44:35,089 --> 00:44:36,591
Blimey, there's a draft.

750
00:44:36,883 --> 00:44:38,176
What a surprise!

751
00:44:38,634 --> 00:44:41,012
Oh, let me look at you.

752
00:44:41,596 --> 00:44:43,681
Ah, six months.

753
00:44:44,098 --> 00:44:46,767
It's like I saw you yesterday.
Isn't it funny?

754
00:44:46,851 --> 00:44:48,227
-The time goes by like that.
-(SNAPS)

755
00:44:48,311 --> 00:44:49,896
(HEAD WHIRRS)

756
00:44:55,151 --> 00:44:57,612
Your wish is my command,
but be careful what you wish for.

757
00:44:57,945 --> 00:44:59,030
The day my father died.

758
00:44:59,322 --> 00:45:01,699
Thought it'd be all grim and stormy.
It's just an ordinary day.

759
00:45:02,116 --> 00:45:03,201
Oh, God, this is it.

760
00:45:03,784 --> 00:45:04,994
He can't die on his own!

761
00:45:05,328 --> 00:45:06,454
(TIRES SCREECHING)

762
00:45:06,829 --> 00:45:08,497
Can I try again?

763
00:45:10,291 --> 00:45:11,459
Oh, gosh, this is it.

764
00:45:11,876 --> 00:45:13,085
Rose! No!

765
00:45:15,087 --> 00:45:17,089
I did it again,
I picked another stupid ape!

766
00:45:17,465 --> 00:45:18,883
It's not like
I've changed history.

767
00:45:19,133 --> 00:45:21,844
Rose, there's a man
alive in the world who wasn't alive before.

768
00:45:22,303 --> 00:45:24,639
The whole world's different
because he's alive!

769
00:45:26,599 --> 00:45:29,644
Time's been damaged,
and they've come to sterilise the wound.

770
00:45:29,810 --> 00:45:31,729
Rose, get in the church!

771
00:45:32,104 --> 00:45:33,147
(SCREAMING)

